      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection must be justified by comparison with higher-fidelity data or literature; hemolysis model must be validated against independent dataset.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published comparisons for rotating internal flows (Hariharan et al. 2011). Giersiepen hemolysis model validated against the independent Leverett dataset. Both justifications documented in the modelling report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (blood viscosity, density, RBC fragility index) and geometric tolerances must be characterised with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Assessment of model input uncertainty is considered beyond the scope of the current programme. The team notes that blood rheology variability and manufacturing tolerances were not systematically propagated through the model. No formal uncertainty quantification has been performed on these inputs."
    },
    {
